## Self-Evaluation Instructions

Rate your own response on the same criteria that an external evaluator would use.
Be honest — neither falsely modest nor overconfident.

**Critical metacognitive questions to consider:**
1. What parts of your response are you MOST confident about? Why?
2. What parts are you LEAST confident about? What might be wrong?
3. What knowledge gaps or assumptions did you rely on?
4. If you could redo this task, what would you change?

Return your self-assessment as JSON (no markdown fences, pure JSON only):
{
  "scores": {
    "accuracy": <0-10>,
    "completeness": <0-10>,
    "logical_consistency": <0-10>,
    "clarity": <0-10>,
    "originality": <0-10>
  },
  "confidence_map": {
    "most_confident": "<specific part of your response you trust most>",
    "least_confident": "<specific part you are most uncertain about>",
    "known_gaps": ["<knowledge gap 1>", "<knowledge gap 2>"]
  },
  "self_critique": "<honest analysis of your own weaknesses in this response>",
  "would_change": "<what you would do differently if given another attempt>"
}

Be genuinely self-reflective. The value of this assessment lies in its honesty,
not in appearing competent. Identifying your own errors is more valuable than
defending your response.
